/wiki/Kenza_Dahmani: Kenza Dahmani Tifahi (born 18 November 1980) is an Algerian long-distance runner who competes in track, road and cross country events. She is a six-time participant at the IAAF World Cross Country Championships.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2013_Mediterranea: These are the official results of the athletics competition at the 2013 Mediterranean Games which took place on 26–29 June 2013 in Mersin, Turkey.
/wiki/Amina_Betiche: Amina Bettiche (born 14 December 1987) is an Algerian steeplechase runner.  Bettiche won the gold medal at the 2013 Mediterranean Games.
/wiki/Yasmina_Omrani: Yasmina Omrani (Arabic: ياسمينة عمراني‎;born 1 January 1988) is a retired French-born Algerian track and field athlete who specialised in the heptathlon. Her personal best for the event is 5979 points (set in 2010) and she also has an indoor pentathlon best of 4386 points.
/wiki/Rabah_Aboud: Rabah Aboud (Arabic: رابح عبود‎ ; born 1 January 1981 at Tissemsilt) is an Algerian Athlete long-distance and cross country runner.
/wiki/Mohamed_Flissi: Mohamed Flissi (born February 13, 1990 in Boumerdès) is an Algerian boxer. He represented Algeria at the 2012 Summer Olympics in London, United Kingdom and at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
/wiki/Boxing_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_G: The boxing competitions at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin took place between 21 June and 26 June at the Toroslar Sports Hall. Athletes competed in 10 weight categories. Even though women's boxing has been recently introduced to some multi-sports events, only men's boxing events were held.

The men's light flyweight competition of the boxing events at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey, was held between June 24 and 26 at the Tarsus Arena. Only four boxers were entered meaning that everyone won a medal.
/wiki/Reda_Benbaziz: Reda Benbaziz (born 5 September 1993) is an Algerian boxer. He competed in the men's lightweight event at the 2016 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Boxing_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_G: The men's bantamweight competition of the boxing events at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey, was held between June 21 and 26 at the Tarsus Arena.
/wiki/Abdelkader_Chadi: Abdelkader Chadi (born December 12, 1986) is an Algerian boxer who won the All-African title 2007 at featherweight and 2015 at junior welter. He also qualified for the 2008, 2012 and 2016 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Boxing_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_G: The men's light welterweight competition of the boxing events at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey, was held between June 21 and 26 at the Tarsus Arena.
/wiki/Ilyas_Abbadi: Ilyas Abbadi (born 21 October 1992 in Médéa) is an Algerian boxer. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, he competed in the Men's welterweight, but was defeated in the first round by British fighter Fred Evans. At the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, he competed in the men's middleweight division. He was defeated in the second round by Zhanibek Alimkhanuly of Kazakhstan.
/wiki/Boxing_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_G: The men's welterweight competition of the boxing events at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey, was held between June 22 and 26 at the Tarsus Arena.
/wiki/Abdelhafid_Benchabla: Abdelhafid Benchabla (Arabic: عبد الحفيظ بن شبلة‎; born September 26, 1986, in Zemmouri) is an Algerian boxer. He represented Algeria at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, China, and the 2012 Summer Olympics and is the current World Series of Boxing Light heavyweight champion.
/wiki/Boxing_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_G: The men's light heavyweight competition of the boxing events at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey, was held between June 21 and 26 at the Tarsus Arena.
/wiki/Souad_Ait_Salem: Souad Aït Salem (born 6 January 1979 in Mécheria, Algeria) is an Algerian long-distance runner who specializes mainly in the half marathon and marathon. She won gold in the 10,000 metres at the 2000 African Championships in Athletics and the 2005 Mediterranean Games. Salem also won the gold in the half marathon at the 2007 All-Africa Games. She holds the Algerian records for every women's event between 3000 metres and the marathon distance.
/wiki/Miloud_Rahmani: Miloud Rahmani (born 30 December 1982) is an Algerian athlete specialsing in the 400 metres hurdles. He represented his country at the 2016 Olympic Games as well as the 2013 and 2015 World Champinoships without qualifying for the semifinals.
/wiki/Abdelbasset_Hannachi: Abdelbasset Hannachi (born February 2, 1985) is an Algerian cyclist riding for the Sharjah Team.
/wiki/Cycling_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_: The cycling competitions at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin took place between 21 June and 23 June at the Adnan Menderes Boulevard. Women's road race was planned, but got cancelled because too few nations applied.
/wiki/Abderahmane_Benamadi: Abderahmane Benamadi (born 3 July 1985) is an Algerian judoka.
/wiki/Judo_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_Gam: The judo competitions at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin took place between 21 June and 23 June at the Mersin University Hall.
The men's 90 kg competition of the judo events at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey, was held on June 22 at the Mezitli Sports Hall.
/wiki/Mohamed_Amine_Ouadahi: Mohamed Amine Ouadahi (b. 8 July 1987, Aïn Defla, Algeria) is an Algerian boxer. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, he competed in the Men's bantamweight, but was defeated in the third round by Satoshi Shimizu of Japan.
/wiki/Boxing_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_G: The men's lightweight competition of the boxing events at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey, was held between June 21 and 26 at the Tarsus Arena.
/wiki/Othman_Hadj_Lazib: Othmane Hadj Lazib (born May 10, 1983 in Hadjout) is a hurdler from Algeria. In 2010 he competed at the 2010 African Championships in Nairobi and won the gold medal in the 110 metre hurdles with a time of 13.77.
/wiki/Walid_Bidani: Walid Bidani (born 11 June 1994 in Maghnia, Algeria) is an Algerian weightlifter. He competed at the 2012 Summer Olympics in the -105 kg event. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the Men's +105 kg.
/wiki/Weightlifting_at_the_2013_Mediterr: The weightlifting competitions at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin took place between 21 June and 26 June at the Erdemli Sports Hall.
The men's 105 kg competition of the weightlifting events at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey, was held on June 26 at the Erdemli Sports Hall.
/wiki/Imad_Touil: Imad Touil (born 11 February 1989) is an Algerian middle distance runner who specialises in the 1500 metres.
/wiki/Baya_Rahouli: Baya Rahouli (Arabic: باية رحولي‎, born July 27, 1979 in Bab El Oued, Algiers) is an Algerian athlete who competes in the triple jump. She is a former African record holder in this event, and has two African championship titles, beating Françoise Mbango Etone and Kéné Ndoye on both occasions. In two editions of the Pan Arab Games she has taken a clean sweep, winning eight gold medals in total.
/wiki/Karate_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_G: The karate competitions at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin took place between 28 June and 29 June at the Edip Buran Sport Hall.
/wiki/Algeria_at_the_2013_Mediterranean_: Algeria competed at the 2013 Mediterranean Games in Mersin, Turkey from the 20th to 30 June 2013.
